    {
      "id": "8ce1332b2ece1007e4683f5fd4fb6cdfc578b881",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-10 08:14:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Is a similar patch also needed in ofd/?\n\nNo, it's not needed in ofd/.\n\nIn ofd_preprw_write(), the grant space check stuff is wrapped in ofd_grant_prepare_write(), which uses remote buffers not local buffers and does not set lnb[n].rc values. Those values are initialized with 0 in dt_bufs_get() after ofd_grant_prepare_write() is run, and are set with -ENOSPC if OBD_BRW_GRANTED flag is not set.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
